===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|lether}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|leþer||leather}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*leþrą||leather}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*létrom||leather}}. Cognate with West Frisian {{m|fy|leare||leather}}, Low German {{m|nds|Ledder||leather}}, {{etyl|nl|-}} {{m|nl|leder}}, {{m|nl|leer||leather}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{m|de|Leder||leather}}, Danish {{m|da|læder||leather}}, Swedish {{m|sv|läder||leather}}, {{etyl|is|-}} {{m|is|leður||leather}}. The Celtic forms ({{etyl|cy|-}} {{m|cy|lledr}}, {{etyl|sga|-}} {{m|sga|lethar}}) ultimately derive from the Germanic.

